metadata.name: Clothesline #1
metadata.description:
Like the interior decorating of any house, Clothes on each rope  are a representative of their consumers.
The clothes are our molds. 
Even if we chose nakedness, the last thing we wore was our mold.
Clothes have something to cover.
Or perhaps something is trying to be sheltered under the clothes.
Here in the most timeless and placeless space in the world someone has hanged some clothes; A place where people always wear white.
